The paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) techniques for automatically scoring short answer questions, which falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses machine learning methods for this task, which falls under the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of information retrieval techniques, which falls under the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of syntactically-informed features, which could potentially fall under the subfield of computational syntax (cs.CY).
